caption: Attribute Dictionary
description: The Attribute Dictionary defines schema attributes and includes references to the events and objects in which they are used.
name: dictionary

attach_time.caption: Attach Time
attach_time.description: The time stamp when the volume was attached to the instance

attachments.caption: List of Attachments
attachments.description: A list of attachments to the resource

cidr_block.caption: CIDR Block
cidr_block.description: The CIDR block of the subnet

cloud_function.caption: Cloud Function
cloud_function.description: The cloud function that processes events

cluster_members.caption: Database Cluster Members
cluster_members.description: List of database instance that are part of the database cluster.

cluster_uid.caption: Cluster UID
cluster_uid.description: The unique identifier for the container cluster

db_cluster.caption: Database Cluster
db_cluster.description: The details of the database cluster.

db_endpoint.caption: Database Endpoint
db_endpoint.description: The database endpoint that is associated with the resource

db_user.caption: Database User
db_user.description: The details of the user account that is the database administrator (e.g. admin).

engine.caption: Engine
engine.description: The engine that is associated with the database

handler.caption: Handler
handler.description: The method in the cloud function that processes events

hosted_zone_uid.caption: Hosted Zone UID
hosted_zone_uid.description: The unique identifier of a hosted zone (e.g. AWS Route 53 Hosted Zone).

imported_time.caption: Imported Date and Time
imported_time.description: The timestamp when the certificate was imported

in_use_by.caption: In Use By
in_use_by.description: List of resources currently using this certificate

in_use_count.caption: In Use Count
in_use_count.description: Count of resources using this image. See specific usage.

instance_profile.caption: Instance Profile
instance_profile.description: Information about the instance profile associated with the compute resource, which provides the resource with permissions to interact with other services

instance_profiles.caption: Instance Profiles
instance_profiles.description: A list of instance profiles associated with the compute resource, which provides the resource with permissions to interact with other services

ip_addresses.caption: IP Address Array
ip_addresses.description: An array of IP addresses (IPv4 or IPv6) associated with the instance. These may include both public and private IP addresses.

ip_count.caption: IP Count
ip_count.description: The number of IP addresses in the subnet

is_delete_on_termination.caption: Is Delete on Termination
is_delete_on_termination.description: Specifies whether the volume will be deleted on instance termination

is_iam_authentication.caption: IAM Database Authentication Enabled
is_iam_authentication.description: Indicates if IAM database authentication is enabled

key_usages.caption: Key Usages
key_usages.description: Key usage defines the purpose of the key contained in the certificate.

ANY.caption: ANY
ANY.description: The public key can be used for any purpose.

CERTIFICATE_SIGNING.caption: CERTIFICATE_SIGNING
CERTIFICATE_SIGNING.description: Used when the public key is used for verifying a signature on certificates.

CRL_SIGNING.caption: CRL_SIGNING
CRL_SIGNING.description: Used when the public key is used for verifying a signature on Certificate Revocation Lists.

CUSTOM.caption: CUSTOM
CUSTOM.description: A custom usage defined by the event source.

DATA_ENCIPHERMENT.caption: DATA_ENCIPHERMENT
DATA_ENCIPHERMENT.description: Used when the public key is used for directly encrypting user data.

DECIPHER_ONLY.caption: DECIPHER_ONLY
DECIPHER_ONLY.description: Used only for deciphering data during key agreement.

DIGITAL_SIGNATURE.caption: DIGITAL_SIGNATURE
DIGITAL_SIGNATURE.description: Used when the public key is used for verifying digital signatures.

ENCIPHER_ONLY.caption: ENCIPHER_ONLY
ENCIPHER_ONLY.description: Used only for enciphering data during key agreement.

KEY_AGREEMENT.caption: KEY_AGREEMENT
KEY_AGREEMENT.description: Used when the sender and receiver of the public key need to derive a key without using encryption.

KEY_ENCIPHERMENT.caption: KEY_ENCIPHERMENT
KEY_ENCIPHERMENT.description: Used when the public key is used for encrypting private or secret keys.

NON_REPUDIATION.caption: NON_REPUDIATION
NON_REPUDIATION.description: Used when the public key is used to verify digital signatures used for non-repudiation services.

last_used_time.caption: Last Used time
last_used_time.description: The time stamp when the resource was last used. See specific usage.

launch_time.caption: Launch Time
launch_time.description: The reported time a device or instance was launched

layers.caption: Cloud Function Layers
layers.description: The list of layers associated with the cloud function.

network_interface.caption: Network Interface
network_interface.description: The Network Interface object describes the type and associated attributes of a physical or virtual network interface.

platform.caption: Platform Name
platform.description: The operating system platform of the image. See specific usage.

registry_uid.caption: Registry UID
registry_uid.description: The unique identifier of a container registry (e.g. AWS ECR Registry ID).

renewable_eligibility.caption: Renewable Eligibility
renewable_eligibility.description: Indicates if the certificate is eligible for renewal

repository_name.caption: Repository Name
repository_name.description: The name of the repository. See specific usage.

security_groups.caption: Array of Security groups
security_groups.description: The array of security groups associated with the resource

snapshot_details.caption: Snapshot Details
snapshot_details.description: The details of the database snapshot.

snapshot_id.caption: Snapshot ID
snapshot_id.description: The storage device snapshot identifier (e.g. snap-1234567890abcdef0).

storage_device.caption: Storage Device
storage_device.description: The storage device that is attached to the instance

subnet_group.caption: Subnet Group
subnet_group.description: The subnet group that is associated with the database

subnet_info.caption: Subnet Information
subnet_info.description: Describes the supporting information about a subnet.

subnet_info_list.caption: List of Subnet Information
subnet_info_list.description: A list of supporting information about a subnet.
